text: Ciladopa (AY-27,110) is a dopamine agonist with a similar chemical structure to dopamine. It was under investigation as an antiparkinsonian agent but was discontinued due to concerns of tumorogenesis in rodents. == References == Category:Dopamine agonists Category:Phenylethanolamines Category:Piperazines Category:Catechol ethers Category:Tropones
